    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "TOtmE",
      "x": -1640,
      "y": 50,
      "name": "labelDS",
      "fill": "#1F2937",
      "content": "📐 Design System",
      "fontFamily": "DM Sans",
      "fontSize": 28,
      "fontWeight": "700"
    },
    {
      "type": "note",
      "id": "Zlm2L",
      "x": 17040,
      "y": 200,
      "name": "note-eML3U-0",
      "width": 340,
      "height": 0,
      "content": "🔴 Critical — Rules Builder Cognitive Load\nThe rules section shows nested AND/OR/NOT groups, colored borders, and sub-groups all at once with no empty state or onboarding hint. A first-time user cannot understand what a 'group' is vs a 'rule'. Add a collapsed empty state with a one-line explainer and only reveal nesting on demand."
    },
    {
      "type": "note",
      "id": "Ql5Wf",
      "x": 17040,
      "y": 400,
      "name": "note-eML3U-1",
      "width": 340,
      "height": 0,
      "content": "🟡 Tip — Operator Labels Feel Technical\n'CONTAINS' and 'LESS_THAN' in SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE read like internal enum values. Change to natural language: 'contains', 'is less than', 'is greater than'. This small change significantly lowers the learning curve for non-technical users."
    },
    {
      "type": "note",
      "id": "rrEHj",
      "x": 17040,
      "y": 600,
      "name": "note-eML3U-2",
      "width": 340,
      "height": 0,
      "content": "🟡 Tip — Form Actions Need a Sticky Footer\nCancel and Create Filter are only visible after scrolling to the bottom of a long form. A sticky bottom bar (with subtle top shadow) would keep the primary CTA always reachable — especially critical when the Rules section grows tall."
    },
    {
      "type": "note",
      "id": "N3C9x",
      "x": 17040,
      "y": 800,
      "name": "note-eML3U-3",
      "width": 340,
      "height": 0,
      "content": "🟡 Tip — 'Add Group' Should Be Visually Subordinate\nBoth 'Add Rule' and 'Add Group' share near-identical styling. Groups are a power-user feature — visually demote 'Add Group' with smaller text or lower contrast to guide first-time users toward the simpler 'Add Rule' action first."
    },
    {
      "type": "note",
      "id": "E7e2Y",
      "x": 17040,
      "y": 1000,
      "name": "note-eML3U-4",
      "width": 340,
      "height": 0,
      "content": "🟡 Tip — Max Notifications/Day Is Context-Dependent\n'Max notifications/day' sits alongside digest toggles but only applies to immediate notifications. When immediate notifications are off, this field should be disabled or hidden. As-is, users may think it caps digest delivery too."
    },
    {
      "type": "note",
      "id": "lHcqd",
      "x": 17040,
      "y": 1200,
      "name": "note-eML3U-5",
      "width": 340,
      "height": 0,
      "content": "🟢 Good — Site Selection Interaction\nThe site badge row (Dealabs / Vinted / LeBonCoin) clearly communicates selected vs unselected through color, border weight, and a checkmark icon. Each site's brand color is consistent. This is an intuitive and scannable affordance."
    },
    {
      "type": "note",
      "id": "VODnl",
      "x": 17040,
      "y": 1400,
      "name": "note-eML3U-6",
      "width": 340,
      "height": 0,
      "content": "🟢 Good — Three-Card Section Structure\nSplitting the form into General / Rules / Notifications cards with section icons and bold headers creates a clean top-to-bottom reading flow. The visual grouping reduces cognitive load and makes it easy to navigate back to a specific section."
    },
    {
      "type": "frame",
      "id": "kF0My",
