    {
      "type": "note",
      "id": "DCfjI",
      "x": 12640,
      "y": 200,
      "name": "note-Xop2B-0",
      "width": 340,
      "height": 0,
      "content": "🟢 Good — Visual Hierarchy\nThe page has a clear dominant title (\"My Filters\"), a supporting subtitle, and a high-contrast primary CTA (\"Create Filter\") anchored top-right. A new user understands the screen purpose in under 3 seconds."
    },
    {
      "type": "note",
      "id": "Kad8l",
      "x": 12640,
      "y": 400,
      "name": "note-Xop2B-1",
      "width": 340,
      "height": 0,
      "content": "🔴 Critical — Missing Empty State\nIf a new user has no filters yet, the 2-column grid renders completely blank. There is no illustration, message, or prompt to guide them. Add an empty state with a short message and a direct \"Create your first filter\" call-to-action."
    },
    {
      "type": "note",
      "id": "u4zL9",
      "x": 12640,
      "y": 600,
      "name": "note-Xop2B-2",
      "width": 340,
      "height": 0,
      "content": "🟡 Tip — Destructive Action Weight\nThe red \"Delete\" button is a solid filled button — same visual weight as the \"Edit\" button. This makes it too easy to accidentally trigger a destructive action. Demote Delete to a ghost or icon-only button so Edit is the natural default action on each card."
    },
    {
      "type": "note",
      "id": "ODAgX",
      "x": 12640,
      "y": 800,
      "name": "note-Xop2B-3",
      "width": 340,
      "height": 0,
      "content": "🟡 Tip — Search Bar Scope & Width\nThe search bar is fixed at ~448px with no label or hint about what it searches (filter names? categories? sites?). Make the placeholder more descriptive (e.g. \"Search by name or category…\") and consider letting it stretch wider to feel less arbitrary on a 1440px canvas."
    },
    {
      "type": "note",
      "id": "wjv1Y",
      "x": 12640,
      "y": 1000,
      "name": "note-Xop2B-4",
      "width": 340,
      "height": 0,
      "content": "🟡 Tip — Card Description Contrast\nThe card description lines (e.g. \"Best gaming hardware and accessories deals\") appear in a very light grey on white. This likely falls below the WCAG AA 4.5:1 contrast ratio for small text. Darken to at least #6B7280 or use a medium grey token."
    }
  ]
}